    Growth Insight

    updated May 12, 2025

    Growing
    OpenAI raised $40 billion in a funding round led by SoftBank, increasing its valuation to $300 billion. This funding round is noted as the largest private tech funding round in history. The investment will support OpenAI's AI research, infrastructure expansion, and the development of new AI models, including the Stargate project, which aims to build AI data centers across the U.S. OpenAI's revenue is projected to triple to $12.7 billion in 2025, up from $3.7 billion in 2024, driven by the success of its paid AI software offerings. Additionally, OpenAI's user base has seen significant growth, reaching 500 million weekly active users, a 33% increase from 400 million in December 2024. The company has also reported a 30% increase in revenue over three months, attributed to a rise in paid subscribers for its ChatGPT service, which grew from 15.5 million to 20 million.

    Legal Proceeding
    OpenAI and Elon Musk are involved in legal disputes, with Musk suing OpenAI for abandoning its original mission, and OpenAI counter-suing Musk for harassment and attempting to derail its shift to a for-profit model. A jury trial is set for next spring.
